{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849214989,"sessionID":"ses_28723cdcbffeotxaCazQMqfwoc","part":{"id":"prt_d78dc90d3001xJ5ViNouDplUUT","messageID":"msg_d78dc84970018ca3YtNBKfv1wQ","sessionID":"ses_28723cdcbffeotxaCazQMqfwoc","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_9695ab49a73a4995b4189985","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"mkdir -p changes/AR-011","description":"Create AR-011 change directory"},"output":"","metadata":{"output":"","exit":0,"description":"Create AR-011 change directory","truncated":false},"title":"Create AR-011 change directory","time":{"start":1775849214978,"end":1775849214987}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775849215010,"sessionID":"ses_28723cdcbffeotxaCazQMqfwoc","part":{"id":"prt_d78dc940c001vNL2T464kU09k3","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78dc84970018ca3YtNBKfv1wQ","sessionID":"ses_28723cdcbffeotxaCazQMqfwoc","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19459,"input":2947,"output":75,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":16437}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775849217541,"sessionID":"ses_28723cdcbffeotxaCazQMqfwoc","part":{"id":"prt_d78dc9e03001CcxrKutKaX39gy","messageID":"msg_d78dc94380010u7qH8gacaY0zE","sessionID":"ses_28723cdcbffeotxaCazQMqfwoc","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849254098,"sessionID":"ses_28723cdcbffeotxaCazQMqfwoc","part":{"id":"prt_d78dca55b001PWzR0Ii56GjVZI","messageID":"msg_d78dc94380010u7qH8gacaY0zE","sessionID":"ses_28723cdcbffeotxaCazQMqfwoc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_82f5bd0ef8104cde9faab224","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing JWT authentication and token issuance in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-011\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires JWT-based authentication to secure API endpoints and enable token-based access control. This includes both JWT validation for incoming requests and token issuance for authenticated clients.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with default configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `jwtEnabled: true` and no explicit JWT configuration\n**WHEN** the router initializes\n**THEN** it SHOULD use default values: secret from environment or config, algorithm \"HS256\", expiry \"1h\"\n\n### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with custom configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance with JWT configuration: `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"`, `jwtExpiry: \"24h\"`, `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n**WHEN** the router initializes\n**THEN** it SHOULD configure RS256 algorithm, 24 hour expiry, and issuer to \"agentcube\"\n\n### Scenario: Router disables JWT authentication\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance with `jwtEnabled: false` (default)\n**WHEN** HTTP requests are received\n**THEN** the router SHOULD NOT validate JWT tokens\n**AND** no JWT middleware SHOULD be applied\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n\n### Scenario: Router validates valid JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and configured secret\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a valid JWT token in Authorization header \"Bearer <valid-token>\"\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n**AND** extract the claims into the request context\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects expired JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with an expired JWT token\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with appropriate error message\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects invalid signature JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a JWT token that has invalid signature\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid signature\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects malformed JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a malformed JWT token (not 3 parts)\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 400 Bad Request with \"malformed token\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router extracts claims from valid JWT\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with valid JWT containing claims: `sub`, `exp`, `roles`\n**THEN** the claims SHOULD be available in request context\n**AND** can be accessed by downstream handlers\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Token Issuance\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT token for valid credentials\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint configured\n**WHEN** a POST request arrives with valid username and password\n**THEN** the router SHOULD authenticate the credentials\n**AND** issue a JWT token with user claims\n**AND** return the token in the response\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured expiry\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtExpiry: \"2h\"`\n**WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n**THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `exp` claim set to current time + 2 hours\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured issuer\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n**WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n**THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `iss` claim set to \"agentcube\"\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects invalid credentials\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint\n**WHEN** a POST request arrives with invalid username or password\n**THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n**AND** NOT issue a JWT token\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Middleware\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from Authorization header\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with header `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token\n**AND** validate it\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from query parameter\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware configured to allow query param\n**WHEN** a request arrives with query param `?token=<token>`\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token from query\n**AND** validate it\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware allows public endpoints\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives at a public endpoint (e.g., `/health`, `/login`)\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD skip JWT validation\n**AND** allow the request through\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware blocks unauthorized access\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives at a protected endpoint without token\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Claims\n\n### Scenario: Router includes user ID in JWT claims\n\n**GIVEN** a user logs in successfully\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include `sub` claim with user identifier\n\n### Scenario: Router includes roles in JWT claims\n\n**GIVEN** a user with roles \"admin\", \"user\" logs in\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include `roles` claim with array [\"admin\", \"user\"]\n\n### Scenario: Router includes custom claims in JWT\n\n**GIVEN** a Router configured with custom claims (e.g., `tenant_id`)\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include the custom claims\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Token Refresh\n\n### Scenario: Router supports token refresh endpoint\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and refresh endpoint configured\n**WHEN** a valid (non-expired) JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n**THEN** a new JWT token SHOULD be issued\n**AND** the new token SHOULD have fresh expiry time\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects refresh with expired token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT refresh enabled\n**WHEN** an expired JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n**THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Key Management\n\n### Scenario: Router loads JWT secret from configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtSecret: \"my-secret-key\"` configured\n**WHEN** JWT validation or issuance occurs\n**THEN** the router SHOULD use \"my-secret-key\" for signing/verification\n\n### Scenario: Router supports RS256 with private key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and private key configured\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD be signed with RS256 using the private key\n\n### Scenario: Router validates RS256 token with public key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and public key configured\n**WHEN** a request arrives with RS256-signed JWT\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate using the public key\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] JWT tokens are validated on protected endpoints\n- [ ] Expired tokens are rejected with 401\n- [ ] Invalid signatures are rejected with 401\n- [ ] Valid tokens expose claims in request context\n- [ ] Login endpoint issues JWT tokens\n- [ ] Token expiry is configurable\n- [ ] Token issuer is configurable\n- [ ] JWT algorithm is configurable (HS256, RS256)\n- [ ] Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n- [ ] Token refresh endpoint works correctly\n- [ ] Custom claims can be included in tokens\n- [ ] Invalid credentials are rejected\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `proposal.md`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775849254084,"end":1775849254094}}}}
